        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13827",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jollytoad",
                        "name": "jollytoad",
                        "displayName": "Mark Gibson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Schema qualified names are already supported.\n\nThroughout Zend_Db classes, wherever a table name is required you can supply:\n\n* a single string containing a qualified or unqualified name.\n  eg: {{\"table\"}} or {{\"schema.table\"}}\n* an array containing the schema as the first item, and name as the second.\n  eg: {{array('schema', 'table')}}\n* a Zend_Db_Expr for the rare occasion that a name contains a dot.\n  eg. {{new Zend_Db_Expr('\"odd.schema\".\"strange.table\"')}}\n\nSo in your code above use:\n{code}\n$this->_name = 'someSchema.someTable';\n{code}\nor\n{code}\n$this->_name = array('someSchema','someTable');\n{code}\n\nThis is all implemented in [Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract::quoteIdentifier()|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Db\/Adapter\/Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract.html#quoteIdentifier],\nand fully supported by Zend_Db_Select, and by Zend_Db_Table.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jollytoad",
                        "name": "jollytoad",
                        "displayName": "Mark Gibson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-30T05:09:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-30T05:09:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13829",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mfcn",
                        "name": "mfcn",
                        "displayName": "Manuel Ferreira",
                        "active": true
                    },
